# CODEOWNERS for agentic-alz
#
# This file is intentionally minimal in v1. Replace `@martinopedal` with the
# real owners (platform team for orchestrator/templates, NetSec for any
# firewall-adjacent code) before going to production. The sibling
# `alz-firewall-policy` repo MUST set NetSec as CODEOWNER on `policies/base/`
# and `lib/`.

* @martinopedal

/orchestrator/                @martinopedal
/templates/                   @martinopedal
/policies/                    @martinopedal
/firewall-policy/             @martinopedal
/.github/workflows/           @martinopedal
/bootstrap/                   @martinopedal

# Squad bootstrap: roadmap + script changes change which work the cloud agent
# can pick up, so they require platform-team review.
/ROADMAP.md                                 @martinopedal
/scripts/squad_bootstrap.py                 @martinopedal
/.github/workflows/squad.yml                @martinopedal
/.github/workflows/copilot-setup-steps.yml  @martinopedal
/schemas/roadmap.schema.json                @martinopedal

# Sensitive allowlists. Both files declare what LLM models / MCP servers the
# orchestrator may reach at runtime. Adding an entry — especially an MCP
# server in `mode: write` — must go through NetSec review.
/docs/models.allowlist.yaml                 @martinopedal
/docs/mcp.allowlist.yaml                    @martinopedal
/orchestrator/agentic_alz/llm/              @martinopedal
/orchestrator/agentic_alz/mcp/              @martinopedal
/policies/mcp_allowlist.rego                @martinopedal

# Agent-instruction surfaces. AGENTS.md and the Copilot custom-instructions
# stub are the canonical guidance every agent (cloud + local) consults; the
# `lint-instructions` CI job verifies they stay in sync. The runtime mirror
# in prompts/system/ is the LLM-stage equivalent and is gated by the
# multi-model judge.
/AGENTS.md                                  @martinopedal
/.github/copilot-instructions.md            @martinopedal
/prompts/system/                            @martinopedal

# Sensitive playbooks. These describe how to change the sensitive surfaces
# above; their structure is enforced by `lint-instructions` and edits must
# be reviewed by the same owner who owns the surface they govern.
/docs/playbooks/04-prompt-or-schema-change.md  @martinopedal
/docs/playbooks/05-policy-change.md            @martinopedal
/docs/playbooks/06-iac-template-change.md      @martinopedal
/docs/playbooks/08-ci-workflow-change.md       @martinopedal
/docs/playbooks/10-research-and-decide.md      @martinopedal

# Decision schema and decision/ research records. Adding a record is a normal
# PR; changing the schema is sensitive (per playbook 04).
/schemas/decision.schema.json               @martinopedal

# Local coordination layer. The .squad/ tree is committed in the open as
# evidence of the agentic workflow that drives this repo, but only Martin
# may change it (per `docs/squad-coordination.md`). The append-only ledger,
# per-agent histories, and orchestration logs all gate on this owner.
/.squad/                                    @martinopedal
/docs/squad.md                              @martinopedal
/docs/squad-coordination.md                 @martinopedal
